<title>FRANCE: Tchuruk wants quick decision on Thomson-CSF.</title>
<headline>Tchuruk wants quick decision on Thomson-CSF.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-07-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>The chairman of Alcatel Alsthom, Serge Tchuruk, said that he wanted the new Socialist-led government to take a decision soon on the future of Thomson-CSF.</p>
<p>The previous government had planned to sell the state's 58 percent stake either to Lagardere Groupe or to Alcatel with Dassault Aviation.</p>
<p>&quot;I have stressed the need for the state to take a position soon on the development of Thomson,&quot; Tchuruk said after a hearing by the defence committee of the National Assembly.</p>
